                if (lexer.token() == JSONToken.RBRACE) {
                    lexer.nextToken();
                    return object;
                } else if (lexer.token() == JSONToken.COMMA) {
                    continue;
                } else {
                    throw new JSONException("syntax error, position at " + lexer.pos() + ", name " + key);
                }
            }

            lexer.skipWhitespace();
            ch = lexer.getCurrent();
            if (ch == ',') {
                lexer.next();
                continue;
            } else if (ch == '}') {
                lexer.next();
                lexer.resetStringPosition();
                lexer.nextToken();

                this.setContext(value, key);

                return object;
            } else {
                throw new JSONException("syntax error, position at " + lexer.pos() + ", name " + key);
            }
        }
    } finally {
        this.setContext(context);
    }
}
```

### Key Improvements:
- **Context Management**: Ensure proper context management when parsing references.
- **Reference Resolution**: Verify reference resolution, particularly for special keys like `$ref`.
- **Exception Handling**: Ensure exceptions are thrown with meaningful messages for syntax errors.

By focusing on these areas, we aim to address potential bugs introduced by changes in reference handling.
